# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Maestro E2E Local Environment Variables
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# This file defines environment variables used when running
# Maestro E2E tests locally.
#
# Copy this file to:
#
#   .env.local  (gitignored)
#
# and adjust the values for your machine.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# How this file is used
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Maestro itself does NOT read `.env` files.
# Environment variables must be passed explicitly using:
#
#   -e KEY=value
#
# Example:
#
#   maestro test tests/landing.yml -e MAESTRO_DEEPLINK=...
#
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Recommended usage (wrapper script)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Use the provided wrapper script:
#
#   apps/betterangels/.maestro/scripts/maestro-e2e.sh
#
# This script:
#
#   - reads `.env.local`
#   - converts each line into `-e KEY=value`
#   - passes them to the Maestro CLI
#
# Example commands:
#
#   yarn e2e:dev
#     - runs all tests on iOS (default)
#
#   yarn e2e:dev -p android
#     - runs all tests on Android
#
#   yarn e2e:dev landing.yml
#   or yarn e2e:dev landing
#     - runs landing.yml file on iOS
#
#  yarn e2e:dev --verbose -p android landing.yml
#     - runs landing.yml with verbose debug output
#
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Manual CLI usage (optional)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# If you prefer to run Maestro directly instead of using the wrapper
# script, pass environment variables explicitly using `-e` and
# specify the platform using `-p`.
#
# Example:
#
#   maestro --verbose -p android test apps/betterangels/.maestro/tests \
#     -e MAESTRO_DEEPLINK="exp+betterangels://expo-development-client/?url=http://192.168.1.198:8081" \
#     -e SOME_OTHER_VAR=value
#
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required variables
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# 1. MAESTRO_DEEPLINK: Deep link used to open the Expo development client.
#   - This must point to your local Expo dev server.
#   - You can obtain this value from the Expo CLI output when running:
#      - yarn nx run betterangels:start (or yarn ba)
#   - Typical link:
#       - exp+betterangels://expo-development-client/?url=http://<LOCAL_IP>:<PORT>
#       - LOCAL_IP: typically `192.168.1.198`
#       - PORT: 8081 (based on app env)
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

MAESTRO_DEEPLINK=exp+betterangels://expo-development-client/?url=http://192.168.1.198:8081
